+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Aq5yV6g8gfH1opA1uJNvfh","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_016Gh3XGNgZ2GtBzxyyMpyoe","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-07-task-queue-design.md","content":"# Task Queue System Design\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Core Classes\n\n1. **`TaskQueueSystem`** - Top-level manager. Manages named queues, global task registry, schedules, shutdown.\n2. **`Queue`** - Internal per-named-queue state: pending tasks (sorted by priority/time), active tasks, DLQ, middleware stack, concurrency settings, handler.\n3. **`Task`** - Data object representing a task with all lifecycle state.\n\n### Task Lifecycle States\n`pending` -> `processing` -> `completed` | `failed` | `cancelled`\n\nFailed tasks may re-enter `pending` (retry) or move to DLQ.\n\n### Data Structures\n\n- **Task registry**: `Map<string, Task>` - global O(1) lookup by ID\n- **Per-queue pending list**: Array sorted on insertion by (priority ASC, availableAt ASC, createdAt ASC)\n- **Per-queue active set**: `Set<string>` - task IDs currently processing\n- **Per-queue DLQ**: `Task[]` - dead-lettered tasks\n- **Dependency graph**: `Map<string, Set<string>>` for dependents, `Map<string, Set<string>>` for dependencies per task\n\n### Key Design Decisions\n\n- **Single class API**: `TaskQueueSystem` is the public API. Methods: `add()`, `process()`, `complete()`, `fail()`, `cancel()`, `getTask()`, `shutdown()`, etc.\n- **Sorted insertion**: When adding to pending, binary-insert by priority then time. Retrieval is O(1) from front.\n- **Dependency resolution**: On `complete()`, check dependents. Unblocked tasks move from blocked -> pending.\n- **Middleware**: Array of `(task, next) => Promise<void>` per queue. Process chains them.\n- **Cron**: Parse subset patterns into \"next occurrence\" calculator. `tick()` method checks all schedules.\n- **Graceful shutdown**: Set flag, reject new adds, await active tasks with timeout, force-cancel remainder.\n\n### File Structure\n\n```\nsrc/\n  index.ts          - Public API exports\n  TaskQueueSystem.ts - Main system class\n  Task.ts           - Task class/interface\n  Queue.ts          - Per-queue internal state\n  types.ts          - Shared types and interfaces\n  cron.ts           - Cron expression parser\n```\n\n### API Surface (exported from index.ts)\n\n```typescript\nclass TaskQueueSystem {\n  add(payload, options?): Task\n  process(queueName?): Task | null\n  complete(taskId): void\n  fail(taskId, error?): void\n  cancel(taskId): void\n  getTask(taskId): Task | null\n  size(queueName?): number\n  getQueueNames(): string[]\n\n  // DLQ\n  getDeadLetterTasks(queueName?): Task[]\n  requeue(taskId): Task\n  clearDeadLetterQueue(queueName?): void\n\n  // Concurrency\n  setConcurrency(queueName, limit): void\n  getConcurrency(queueName): { limit: number, active: number }\n\n  // Progress\n  updateProgress(taskId, percent, message?): void\n  onProgress(taskId, callback): () => void\n\n  // Recurring\n  addSchedule(id, cronExpr, queueName, payload, options?): void\n  removeSchedule(id): void\n  getSchedules(): Schedule[]\n  tick(): Task[]\n\n  // Middleware\n  use(queueName, middleware): void\n  setHandler(queueName, handler): void\n\n  // Shutdown\n  shutdown(options?): Promise<ShutdownResult>\n  onShutdown(callback): void\n}\n```\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":314,"cache_read_input_tokens":25653,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":314},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"41a2633b-441a-43ad-b989-10aed8aa6cfb","uuid":"c0219f1e-e023-4379-912c-08dfdf3032c1"}
